            "content": "# Thread Title Generator Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (if subagents available) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Auto-generate thread titles from first user message + first LLM response, using async non-blocking title generation.\n\n**Architecture Notes (from code review):**\n- `SessionStore.update_chat(chat_id, title)` already exists ‚Äî reuse it\n- `EventTranslator` is stateless ‚Äî add `__init__` with tracking state\n- UI (chat.html) uses **HTMX** for interactivity ‚Äî title update should use HTMX request, not WebSocket\n- `WebAdapter` websocket closes after `run_task` returns ‚Äî background task cannot send on it\n\n**Revised Architecture:**\n1. `EventTranslator` detects first assistant complete ‚Üí emits `TITLE_REQUESTED` `AgentEvent`\n2. `WebAdapter` handles `TITLE_REQUESTED` by spawning background title generation task\n3. Background task calls `SessionStore.update_chat()` to persist title\n4. Title update triggers HTMX refresh of sidebar chat list (existing pattern)\n\n**Tech Stack:** DeepAgents, LangGraph, FastAPI, aiosqlite, HTMX\n\n---\n\n## Chunk 1: Internal Event Types & EventTranslator Updates\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/agent_tui/services/deep_agents/events.py` (optional, for type hinting)\n- Modify: `src/agent_tui/domain/protocol.py` ‚Äî add `TITLE_REQUESTED` to `EventType`\n- Modify: `src/agent_tui/services/deep_agents/event_translator.py` ‚Äî add state tracking\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add TITLE_REQUESTED to EventType enum**\n\nIn `src/agent_tui/domain/protocol.py`:\n\n```python\nclass EventType(Enum):\n    # ... existing types ...\n    TITLE_REQUESTED = \"title_requested\"\n```\n\nAnd add corresponding fields to `AgentEvent` dataclass:\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass AgentEvent:\n    # ... existing fields ...\n    user_message: str = \"\"\n    assistant_response: str = \"\"\n    thread_id: str = \"\"\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Update EventTranslator with state tracking**\n\nModify `EventTranslator` to track first user/assistant and emit `TITLE_REQUESTED`:\n\n```python\nclass EventTranslator:\n    def __init__(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize translator with state for title generation tracking.\"\"\"\n        self._first_user_message: str = \"\"\n        self._first_assistant_response: str = \"\"\n        self._first_assistant_done: bool = False\n\n    def translate(self, event: dict[str, Any]) -> Iterator[AgentEvent]:\n        # ... existing code, add yield from self._handle_chain_stream below ...\n\n    def _handle_chain_stream(self, data: dict[str, Any], event: dict[str, Any]) -> Iterator[AgentEvent]:\n        \"\"\"Handle on_chain_stream events for message chunks.\"\"\"\n        name = data.get(\"name\", \"\")\n        if name == \"content_block_delta\":\n            content = data.get(\"data\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\")\n            if content:\n                # Track first human message\n                if not self._first_user_message:\n                    # This is the first human message\n                    pass\n                yield AgentEvent(\n                    type=EventType.MESSAGE_CHUNK,\n                    text=content,\n                )\n```\n\nActually, tracking first messages is tricky with streaming chunks. Simpler approach: use `on_chain_end` to emit `TITLE_REQUESTED` if we have first messages tracked.\n\nBetter approach ‚Äî track messages in the `AgentEvent` flow differently:\n\nIn `EventTranslator._handle_chain_end`, if `self._first_assistant_response` is set and `self._first_assistant_done` is False:\n1. Set `self._first_assistant_done = True`\n2. Yield `TITLE_REQUESTED` with both messages\n\nNeed to track first messages somewhere. Options:\n- A) Store in EventTranslator instance state\n- B) Extract from the event data directly in `_handle_chain_end`\n\nOption B is cleaner ‚Äî `_handle_chain_end` has